\b \cf0 ###Go to Minister\'92s Island in St. Andrews 
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri720

\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri720

\f0 \cf0 ![Nova Scotia Road Trip](thumb_IMG_E0152_mansion2.jpg \'93Mansion\'94) \
Our hosts in St. Stephen recommended (Minister\'92s Island) [https://www.ministersisland.net/) to us, and so on our way through Canada to Nova Scotia, we stopped. They told us that you have to get to Minister\'92s Island early in the morning because the tide rises and you can\'92t get off the island. \
\
They heard a story once where one man wanted to take pictures of the tide coming into the island so he stayed on it longer than he should have stayed. He parked his car on the island, and when the tide rose it took the car with it. People never found the car, but the man taking photos survived. Make sure you get to the island early, and leave when you are supposed to leave.\
\
When you drive up to Minister\'92s Island, it\'92s really stunning. There are large stones and pebbles on the ground with larger rocks long the shoreline near the water. There are tress, so many trees, in the distance. I felt like it was just impossible for nature to look that beautiful. \
\
Ministers Island was the summer home of Sir William Van Horne. He was an artist and his paintings hung inside the mansion. You can see the barn, gardens and creamery. Minister\'92s Island is definitely a beautiful place to check out. \
\
